parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical system failures, leading to intermittent malfunctions of various components, such as speedometers, cruise control, and power windows, which can be distracting and increase the risk of accidents.
